Installation of go on debian debian 8.5 amd64


1. Download go tarball for Linux:
$ wget https://storage.googleapis.com/golang/go1.6.3.linux-amd64.tar.gz (81MB)

SHA256: cdde5e08530c0579255d6153b08fdb3b8e47caabbe717bc7bcd7561275a87aeb
--golang.org/dl/

$ sha256sum go1.6.3.linux-amd64.tar.gz 
cdde5e08530c0579255d6153b08fdb3b8e47caabbe717bc7bcd7561275a87aeb  go1.6.3.linux-amd64.tar.gz

Looks good

2. Install go directory under /usr/local:
$ tar -C /usr/local -xvf go1.6.3.linux-amd64.tar.gz

--golang.org/doc/install

3. Add GOROOT and PATH to ~/.bashrc:
GOROOT=/usr/local/go
PATH=${PATH}:${GOROOT}
export PATH


